overview: The user initiated a project to enhance their Sleep Questionnaire
  Application by adding a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for
  data access, and an authentication system. After an initial codebase
  evaluation, a plan was developed to integrate a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB)
  via Prisma, create API endpoints for questionnaire submission and data
  retrieval (including CSV export), and build a simple admin dashboard. The
  authentication system was first implemented with custom session management,
  but was later refactored to a more streamlined approach using Next.js
  middleware and a basic cookie, significantly simplifying the code. The project
  also involved updating the questionnaire's demographic fields to align with
  the SOW. The database was successfully set up, and the application is now
  ready for comprehensive testing of all new functionalities.
